clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Ancestim in combination with filgrastim is indicated for the setting of autologous peripheral blood progenitor cell transplantation in patients at risk of poor peripheral blood progenitor cell mobilisation L1090 The use of ancestim with filgrastim will generate a sustained increase in the number of peripheral blood progenitor cells capable of engraftment It is used for mobilization of progenitor cells from the bone marrow to the peripheral blood with or withouth mobilizing chemotherapy The harvested progenitor cells can be used for transplant following myelosuppressive or myeloablative therapies L1089

contraindications.disease: Ancestim was not genotoxic for gene mutation or chromosomal damage and it did not have any effect in fertility L1089
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Ancestim action on hemotopeitic progenitor cells stimulates its proliferation differentiation commitment and functional activation This stimulation results in an increase on circulating peripheral blood progenitor cells like CD34 granulocyte macrophage colony forming units and erythroid burst forming units L1089

incompatibilities.description: The risk or severity of pulmonary toxicity can be increased when Ancestim is combined with Cyclophosphamide
